d. Provide this Office with copies of the MOA, project proposals, and other relevant documents within five (5) days from the date of MOA execution;
e. Direct the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to process the disbursement vouchers for the refund of unutilized funds to the source agencies, where applicable;
f. Consider undertaking a one-time cleansing of all dormant accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2023-008 dated August 17, 2023, to improve the accuracy and reliability of the accounting records; and
g. Institutionalize a monitoring mechanism to regularly track the status of fund utilization and project implementation, and ensure the prompt submission of liquidation reports and the refund of any unutilized balances to the source agencies.

a. Strengthen internal controls to ensure that charges are allocated to the correct fund based on the original budget and fund guidelines; 
b. Implement more robust procedures for reviewing budget allocations and actual fund charges to prevent errors; and
c. Reconcile budgeted funds with actual allocations on a regular basis to ensure accurate reporting and compliance.

a. Require the contractor to fully complete the elevator project strictly in accordance with the original contract specifications, within a non-extendable period, and subject to LGU final inspection and acceptance;
b. Impose liquidated damages against the contractor for unjustified delays pursuant to Section 68 of RA 9184, to recover losses from project slippage and delayed service delivery;
