a. During the annual planning, adopt realistic income estimates to ensure that income projections are more accurate based on reasonable and attainable figures, as this will serve as a more reliable foundation for budget preparation, set a realistic spending ceiling, and support the goal of achieving economic viability; 
b. Implement a proactive budget monitoring by establishing a system for quarterly monitoring of the actual income, with corresponding adjustments made in the levels of spending; 
c. Strengthen procurement and project management processes to avoid delays in the implementation of loan-funded capital outlay projects; 
d. Optimize personnel cost management such that the excess cost of PS requirements of regular staff that is depleting the MEEDO funds be treated as staff on detail, to be included in the computation of the 45 percent PS Limitation for the General Fund-Proper; and
e. Re-assess and rationalize MEEDO operations by conducting a comprehensive re-evaluation of the viability of the MEEDO units that are not generating sufficient income and rationalizing their operations and personnel structure to help improve efficiency and financial sustainability.

