We recommended and the Management agreed to the following:

a.	The LCE direct the HRMO to formulate policy and procedures and staffing pattern in engaging and managing JO personnel and internal controls to ensure that they are performing the required task and reporting to the official station, and bases of assigning wage rates;

b.	The Sangguniang Bayan, upon review and deliberation, institutionalize the policy and procedures and staffing pattern in engaging and managing JO personnel, as prepared by the HRMO, by legislating it into an ordinance;

c.	The HRMO as the office who is tasked to regulate, control and ensure the human resource welfare, support the department heads in monitoring and regulating the JO personnel and help the LCE in implementing the guidelines, policies and procedures in the hiring of JO that will be formulated.

We recommended and the Management agreed that:

a.	The HRMO design its organizational structure, implement staffing pattern and analyze actual demand of workforce based on service requirements, to come up with a most beneficial decision for the hiring of personnel; 

b.	The Management to utilize and fully operationalize its recruitment process through its Human Resource Management Office (HRMO) to ensure that personnel who possess the qualification standards of funded plantilla positions are employed to achieve the purpose/s for which funds are appropriated.

We recommended and the Management agreed that:

