The Municipal Mayor create an Inventory Committee for the sole purpose of conducting a one-time cleansing of the Municipality’s PPE which shall be composed of adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory in three months or less and shall be temporary relieved from their regular duties to devote their full time in the conduct of the physical inventory taking until the same is completed and which shall have at least one member each from the Accounting and Property units;

The Inventory Committee prepare a PIP duly approved by the Municipal Mayor to include the specific assignment/duties of its members, the cut-off date and a schedule specifying the dates and locations of the inventory taking activities from start up to the targeted completion of the physical inventory;

The Inventory Committee complete the inventory taking of PPE and come up with a RPCPPE for reconciliation; 

Conduct disposal of unserviceable PPE by accomplishing the required Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Properties pursuant to Annex 51 of the Manual on NGAS for LGUs which will serve as the basis in dropping said items in the RPCPPE and books of accounts;

If accountability/responsibility over missing PPEs could not be pinpointed after investigation, authority for derecognition thereof from the books of accounts may be requested from the COA, in accordance with Paragraph 8 of COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020; and

The Municipal Mayor, Inventory Committee, Property Unit, Accounting Unit and concerned Municipal Government Department Heads and concerned employees be mindful of their respective share of compliance on the specific guidelines as to preliminary activities prior to the conduct of inventory taking, the inventory taking itself and reconciliation of PPE, in order to accomplish the main objective of cleansing the PPE of the Municipality.

The Local Chief Executive require each office to strictly comply with the preparation of the serially numbered Driver’s Trip Ticket and other monthly reports for monitoring fuel consumption as prescribed in the Circular;

The Municipal Accountant as the internal control officer verify the veracity of fuel consumption reported by the driver in the trip tickets prior to recording expense by checking the fuel reading in the vehicle odometer against the balance shown in the driver’s trip ticket prior to recording of gasoline expense and discourage recording of fuel consumption without the duly filled-out trip tickets;

The concerned Municipal Department Heads require drivers under their supervision to report defective odometer and engine meter readers immediately; and

The Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption and Monthly Report of Official Travels shall be submitted to the Auditor for verification purposes to determine the reasonableness of fuel consumed during the period.

The Local Chief Executive require the Municipal Planning and Development Council to prepare and include the specific program, projects and activities that partake the nature of investments and capital expenditures in the 20% Development Fund Plan;

