The Municipal Treasurer prepare a duly certified list showing the name of the taxpayers  and the amount due and collectible for the year and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant to serve as the basis in setting up the beginning balance of RPT/SET Receivable in the books of accounts.  In such manner, the related receivable account and deferred liability will be presented fairly in the financial statements;
The Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant conduct reconciliation of records to establish a realistic balance of receivables for the RPT Taxes and SET Taxes so that necessary adjustment(s) in the books of accounts can be effected for a more realistic presentation of the balances in the financial statements;
The Municipal Treasurer religiously update the individual Real Property Tax Account Register (RPTAR) or Taxpayer’s Index Card every time a payment is received from the taxpayer which shall serve as the basis in the preparation of the List of Delinquent Real Property Taxpayers as of the end of the year, the total of which shall equal the RPT/SET Receivable at year end; and
The Local Chief Executive (LCE), Municipal Treasurer and other concerned Municipal Officials exert concerted efforts to intensify collections of long outstanding RPT and SET Receivables including the interest thereon so that more development programs may be implemented for the benefit of the constituents.

